enhanced_by.reason: The next method relies on the object and the state of removeAllowed, which are set during the constructor initialization.
The reset method sets the beforeFirst flag to true, which is a prerequisite state for the next method to function correctly.
The hasNext method checks the state of beforeFirst and removed, which are also checked in the next method to determine if the next element can be returned.
The remove method changes the state of removed, which affects the behavior of the next method when called subsequently.
